### **Staking V2 Launch Preparation & Tokamak zk-EVM implementation**

# ![][image1]2025 Tokamak Network(TON) Bi-Weekly Report \#4 : 4/15 \~ 4/30

### Highlight

Two headlines from the projects of Tokamak Network:

1. The second version of Tokamak Staking (a.k.a. Staking V2) is about to be launched.  
2. Tokamak zk-EVM is fully implemented.

### Ecosystem

#### 1.1. Staking Update

#### ![][image2]

As of April 30th, 2025, the total amount of staked TON has reached 23,751,543 TON. By staking with Tokamak Network, you contribute to this growing total and enjoy several benefits:

1\) Approximately [31% APY](https://simple.staking.tokamak.network/home)

2\) Various benefits such as airdrops

3\) The rights to participate in Tokamak Network DAO’s operations and decision-making process

#### 1.2. Transaction

In the past two weeks, Tokamak Network has recorded 356 TON transactions and 786 WTON transactions.

#### 1.3. Market Cap

![][image3]

Tokamak Network recorded a market capitalization of $61.55M with a total issuance of 93,008,692 TON on April 30th. Over the past two weeks, TON token price changed from a high of $1.24 to a low of $$1.17, and the total trading volume was $32.07M. For the latest information about total supply and price, please click on [Price Dashboard](https://price.tokamak.network/#/).

### Technology Development

#### 2.1. Tech Development

Tokamak Network is an On-demand Layer 2 Platform and strives to provide various Layer 2 protocols to its users.![][image4]

* There have been 345 commits across 19 repositories in the Tokamak Network GitHub from April 15 to April 30\. The table above breaks down the number of commits by thematic pool, helping users understand the areas of active development. For more details on each repository and its progress, please visit the [Tokamak Network GitHub](https://github.com/tokamak-network).

2.2 Developing a Sybil-Resistance System for Decentralized Applications([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/03cc941223844f30ba4473e98b1275a7?pvs=25)).

* Refactored the sequencer package and tested user transaction functions in the smart contract.

2.3 Developing Zero-Knowledge Proof-Based On-Demand Rollups([Overview](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://medium.com/tokamak-network/project-tokamak-zk-evm-67483656fd21&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1734490765043963&usg=AOvVaw0KzcrtZJnAnxzX0oQiIp8Q)).

* The Rust backend algorithm of Tokamak zk-SNARK is ready to use. Now the Tokamak zk-EVM can be demonstrated: converting an ERC-20 transaction for the TON contract to a zk-proof.

#### 2.4. Developing Decentralized Staking and Governance([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/49e44e989c514bd683e077c01cc8f143?pvs=25)).

* Published articles introducing Staking V2 and the Staking & DAO audit report.  
* Preparing to open Staking V2.

#### 2.5. Advancing Developer-Centric Appchain Infrastructure([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/1433390669554ae5b09e400f4c9c0fd4?pvs=25)).

* First-round testing of Rollup Hub SDK v1 completed; preparing for second round.  
* Conducted cross-trade demo using two appchains deployed via SDK v1; preparing for audit.  
* An MVP implementation plan for integrating Celestia DA with the Thanos stack has been prepared, and development will begin soon.

### Community

#### 3.1. Ethereum and Layer 2 market

##### As of April 30, the Layer 2 market cap stands at $8.4 billion, reflecting a 0.62% increase over the past 24 hours. This accounts for 0.29% of the total cryptocurrency market cap. The Layer 2 sector also recorded $988 million in trading volume during the same 24-hour period.

3.2. FAQ

These are some of the FAQs from the community. Please check the section below.

* **How to contribute to the Tokamak Network?**

1. **Grant program**: create your own project and apply for [GranTON](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Grant-Program-GranTON-f2384b458ea341a0987c7e73a909aa21?pvs=4)**.**  
2. **Full time**: [apply for a full-time position](https://recruit.wanted.co.kr/p/QVxQS0MVRm5HWEpb) with compensation and get paid in USDT/USDC in addition to the [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) grant paid by GranTON projects.  
3. **Part time**: apply for a part-time position in GranTON projects to expect receiving [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) rewards. Please contact the [project leader (owner)](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Onboarding-523bc627bd374326b5dfbec3d3b0a8e1?pvs=21) directly and discuss with them.

* **How can I contact you if I would like to collaborate with the Tokamak Network team?**

  Thank you for your interest in collaborating with the Tokamak Network team. We are open to various forms of collaboration that foster Tokamak Network ecosystem growth and value.

  To discuss a potential collaboration, please send a brief description of your proposal to hello@tokamak.network, and we will review it and respond as soon as possible.
